Please refer to the recipe card for Step 1.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.

> Our riff on pistou (the Provençal take on pesto) includes nutty sunflower seeds and a touch of tangy red wine vinegar—and it's just the thing to make these couscous bowls sing. First, seasoned chicken cutlets are seared until browned, then roasted with tender red peppers and zucchini to a juicy finish. That's all served atop pearl couscous and kale, enriched with dates and a spoonful of herby pistou. The chicken is drizzled with even more pistou for a colorful (and delicious) finishing touch.

@chicken cutlets{10%ounce} seasoned with @oregano-garlic seasoning{1.5%teaspoon}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}.

Heat a #large pan{} over medium-high heat with @cooking oil{} until hot. Add the chicken cutlets and sear until browned on both sides, about ~{3%minutes}.

Transfer the chicken to a #baking sheet{}.

Add @roasted red peppers{2.25%ounce}(tender) and @zucchini{1%unit} to the baking sheet.

Roast in the #oven{} until the chicken is cooked through and the vegetables are tender, about ~{15%minutes}.

> The chicken is done when internal temperature reaches 165°.

Meanwhile, prepare the pearl couscous according to package instructions.

Prepare the @lacinato kale{2.75%ounce}(chopped) and @dates{3/4%ounce}(pitted and chopped).

Prepare the @basil pistou{2.75%ounce}.

Serve the roasted chicken cutlets atop @toasted pearl couscous{1/2%cup} and kale.

Add the dates and drizzle with @basil pistou{} for a colorful and delicious finishing touch.

Top with a spoonful of pistou for extra flavor.

Season with @salt{} and @pepper{} to taste.

Serve with @?butter{1%tablespoon} to enrich the couscous bowls with a silky finish.